ğŸš€ What is V8?
V8 = JavaScript Engine created by Google
It is the program that runs JavaScript code.
ğŸ‘‰ Without V8, JavaScript cannot run.
So:
Your JS code â†’ V8 â†’ Machine code â†’ CPU executes
ğŸ§  Why V8 Exists
Computers understand only:
Binary (0 and 1)

But you write:
let x = 5;

So something must translate JS â†’ machine language.
ğŸ‘‰ That translator = V8 engine
ğŸŒ Where V8 is Used

V8 runs JavaScript in:
Google Chrome
Microsoft Edge (Chromium)
Node.js
Deno
Many servers

So when you run:
node app.js
ğŸ‘‰ Node uses V8 internally.

